post_text:
Parents and Community:

Education services are to still be delivered during the Stay at Home Order from the Governor. We will be following the State Board of Education guidance on closure until April 20th. GFSD will be handing out breakfast and lunch on a grab and go basis on April 1st, 2nd, 7th, 8th, 13th, and 14th from the foyer at the main entrance to the school building from 9:00am-12:30pm.

Student work that was delivered/handed out previously is to be turned in on April 13th and 14th at the foyer as well. This will be from 8:30am-3:00pm each day. At this time students and parents will also pick up the next weeks worth of work from teachers in the foyer.

Teachers will be available through phone and email on April 1,2,7,8,13,& 14 for assistance if needed. Some teachers are planning to hold zoom meetings to be available via the internet in order to assist students and parents as well. Feel free to ask for guidance on work when needed!

Stay safe everybody

Sincerely,

Cody Fisher

Cody Fisher
Superintendent
Glenns Ferry Jt School District 192

post_text:
Following CDC guidelines:
Glenns Ferry School District will hold classes tomorrow, Monday, March 16th and into the week as long as public health safety allows. If a student is sick, it is recommended that they stay home.

We will continue to monitor information and recommendations on the COVID-19 situation consistently and will make decisions accordingly. If changes are made to whether or not school is open, we will notify the public immediately.

post_text: Based upon current information and guidance from the CDC and the State of Idaho on the Coronavirus we feel the best decision at this time is for Glenns Ferry School District classes to continue as normal. We will have school on Monday, March 16th. We will continue to monitor the situation and information we receive on a consistent basis and will notify you if a change in scheduling or classes becomes necessary. Thank you for your support in this matter.

Community Members: Feel free to join in our dress up days (elementary, middle, or high school) and post your pics on our school Facebook page! We would LOVE to see your GF Spirit! 🧡🖤

Remember, too, Kelly Jo Martinez at Serendipity Designs has some awesome Pilot gear you can purchase now!!

The 1A state baseball tournament is at the Uhl/Smith Baseball Field right here on Glenns Ferry beginning tomorrow with the first game starting at 9 am and will end on Saturday. The Pilots play their first game at 5 pm tomorrow evening.
Prices Each Day:
United Dairyman pass and ISAA pass, Free
Students K-6, $4
7th grade and up with an activity card, $4
Senior citizens 60 and over, $4
Students 7th grade and up without an activity card, $5
Adults, $5

Please come out and support our Pilot Baseball team as they battle for a state title!

HOMECOMING WEEK 2018

September 15 Main Street clean up 10 am.

September 17 Dress up day Freshman Character and Career Day.
March of Freshman characters followd by Macho Volleyball 10 am
Miss Pilot performances must be approved.

September 18 Dress up day Blast from the Past (any generation).

September 19 Dress up day Sports Day (any athletic attire)
Powderpuff at 7 pm and Miss Pilot at halftime.

September 20 Dress up day Spirit Day
Formal Coronation and Pep Rally in the high school gym starting at 1:30 pm, entire district and community invited.
Homecoming parade downtown along 1st Street and pep rally at chamber corner.

September 21 Football game at 7 with Royalty being announced at halftime.
Announce community spirit stick winner at halftime.
Bonfire after the game weather permitting.

September 22 Homecoming dance 8-11 pm in the multi purpose room.
